{"title_page": "Andrew Law (financier)", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=June 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Andrew Law\n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Andrew Eric Law\n| birth_date         = {{bya|1966|06}}\n| birth_place        = [[Cheadle Hulme]], [[Stockport]], England\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = British\n| other_names        = \n| known_for          = \n| education          = [[Cheadle Hulme High School]]<br/>[[Sheffield University]]\n| employer           = [[Caxton Associates]]\n| occupation         = Financier\n| networth           = {{increase}} {{GBP}}485 million <small>(Sunday Times Rich List, 2019)</small>\n| spouse             = Zoe Law\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n}}\n'''Andrew Eric Law''' (born June 1966) is a British financier, hedge fund manager and philanthropist. He serves as the chairman and chief executive officer of [[Caxton Associates]], a hedge fund headquartered on [[Berkeley Square]] in London.\n\n==Early life==\nAndrew Eric Law was born in June 1966,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/tGHT8YEuYkqXopv_SB07iDpSVQ4/appointments|title=Andrew Eric LAW - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House)|author=|date=|website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref> and raised in [[Cheadle Hulme]] near [[Stockport]], England.<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\">Andrew Cave, [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/10081784/Outspoken-hedge-fund-boss-who-made-the-journey-from-city-to-city.html Outspoken hedge fund boss who made the journey from city to city], ''The Daily Telegraph'', 26 May 2013</ref><ref name=\"speakersforschoolsandrew\">{{cite web|url=http://www.speakers4schools.org/speakers/andrew-law|title=Andrew Law \u2013 Speakers for Schools|author=|date=|website=www.speakers4schools.org|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref> His father was a mechanical engineer and his mother was a nurse.<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/> He was educated at [[Cheadle Hulme High School]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/> He graduated from the [[University of Sheffield]] in [[Sheffield]], [[South Yorkshire]], with a [[British undergraduate degree classification|First Class honours degree]] in Economics in 1987.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lawfamilycharitablefoundation.org/|title=Law Family Charitable Foundation - Andrew & Zo\u00eb Law|author=|date=|website=www.lawfamilycharitablefoundation.org|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"socialfinanceboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.socialfinance.org.uk/about-us/board-and-team/|title=Social Finance: Board|author=|date=|website=socialfinance.org.uk|accessdate=29 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021212608/http://www.socialfinance.org.uk/about-us/board-and-team/|archive-date=21 October 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"cnbc\">[https://www.cnbc.com/id/48162061#. Andrew E. Law], ''[[CNBC]]''</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHe started his career in finance at County NatWest, now known as [[NatWest]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/><ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> He then worked as a trader at the [[Chemical Bank]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/><ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/><ref name=\"cnbc\"/> In 1996, he joined [[Goldman Sachs]], later becoming a managing director, where he oversaw [[Investment banking|FICC]].<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/><ref name=\"cnbc\"/>\n\n=== Caxton Associates ===\nHe started working at Caxton Associates in London in 2003.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\" /><ref name=\"cnbc\" /> In 2008, he became its Chief Investment Officer.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\" /><ref name=\"socialfinanceboard\" /><ref name=\"ftsamjones\">Sam Jones, [http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/0ecc2df4-3679-11e3-8ae3-00144feab7de.html Quiet Caxton chief refuses to shout about $1bn gain], ''Financial Times'', 20 October 2013</ref> Since 2012, he has served as its chairman and chief executive officer.<ref name=\"socialfinanceboard\" /><ref name=\"cnbc\" /><ref name=\"ftsamjones\" /> Law is the company's main shareholder.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/sunday-times-rich-list-2019-profiles-251-298-lkqrqgnkb|title=Rich List 2019: profiles 251-298=|last=Times|first=The Sunday|date=2019-05-12|access-date=2019-09-20|language=en|issn=0140-0460}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Caxton Associates made \u00a37.3 million profit, down from \u00a395.8 million in 2016.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\n==Political affiliations==\nBetween May 2010 and January 2015, he donated \u00a3947,911 to the [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]], making him its 11th biggest donor in this period.<ref name=\"ftelizabeth\">Elizabeth Rigby, Gavin Jackson, George Parker, 'Tories double number of big City donors in five years: Miliband attacks 'party of Mayfair hedge funds and Monaco tax avoiders',' ''Financial Times'', 5 February 2015, p. 1, http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/11306cd0-ac94-11e4-beeb-00144feab7de.html#axzz3wTjPW2T4</ref> In May 2017, he gave \u00a3250,000 to the Conservative Party.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cityam.com/264987/party-donors-biggest-names-bank-rolling-conservative|title=Party donors: Here are the big names bank-rolling the Conservative campaign|first=Helen|last=Cahill|date=18 May 2017|website=cityam.com|accessdate=28 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\nHe co-chairs the Law Family Charitable Foundation with his wife.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> They support many non-profit organisations, including the [[Policy Exchange]], a think tank based in [[Westminster]].<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> In 2014, they donated \u00a31&nbsp;million to [[The Lowry]] in [[City of Salford|Salford]], where the spaces inside the Main Gallery were renamed The Andrew and Zo\u00eb Law Galleries.<ref name=\"manchestershelina\">Shelina Begum, [http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/business/businessman-andrew-law-wife-zo-7354917 Businessman Andrew Law and wife Zo\u00eb donate \u00a31m to The Lowry], ''Manchester Evening News'', 2 July 2014</ref><ref name=\"thelowrywebsite\">[http://www.thelowry.com/news/2014/07/01/the-lowry-announces-largest-ever-private-donation-and-achieves-5m-capital-funding-target The Lowry announces largest ever private donation and achieves \u00a35m capital funding target], The Lowry, 1 July 2014</ref>\n\nLaw is the chairman of the board of Trustees of Speakers for Schools, which invites public speakers to state schools in the UK.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> He spoke at the [[Trinity C.E. High School]] in Manchester.<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/> He also serves on the Board of Trustees of [[Social Finance UK|Social Finance]].<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> Additionally, he is a patron of the Hotcourses Foundation, which helps vulnerable schoolchildren in [[Kenya]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nyumbani.org.uk/patrons/|title=Patrons of Nyumbani UK|author=|date=|website=nyumbani.org.uk|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn an op ed published in ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' in 2014, he called for hedge fund managers to be more philanthropic.<ref>Andrew Law, [http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/andrew-law/the-hedge-fund-formula-fo_b_4115015.html The Hedge Fund Formula For Philanthropy], ''The Huffington Post'', 23 January 2014</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Zo\u00eb Law<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/>, a photographer whose portfolio includes the recent exhibition ''LIFE'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.list.co.uk/event/1032513-zoe-law-life/|title=Zoe Law: LIFE|website=The List|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-23}}</ref>,  which features portraits of 21 people who have cancer. The exhibition, which was displayed at The Lowry in Salford Quays in 2019 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.northernsoul.me.uk/photo-gallery-life-an-exhibition-by-photographer-zoe-law-at-salfords-the-lowry/|title=Photo Gallery: LIFE by Zo\u00eb Law, The Lowry, Salford|date=2019-04-15|website=Northern Soul|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-23}}</ref>, was set up to raise awareness of the cancer support provided by the [[Maggie's Centres]]. Zo\u00eb Law was previously a make-up artist whose clients included the British singer [[Dido (singer)|Dido.]] \n\nAccording to The [[Sunday Times Rich List]] in 2019, Law is worth \u00a3485 million.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nHe is a supporter of the football team, [[Manchester City F.C.]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\" /> He owns \"Manchester City vs Sheffield United\", a 1938 painting by [[L. S. Lowry]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Law, Andrew}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Cheadle Hulme]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Sheffield]]\n[[Category:Goldman Sachs people]]\n[[Category:English hedge fund managers]]\n[[Category:English financial businesspeople]]\n[[Category:English philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) people]]\n[[Category:People educated at Cheadle Hulme School]]\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) donors]]\n[[Category:Bankers from London]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=June 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Andrew Law\n| image              = \n| image_size         = \n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Andrew Eric Law\n| birth_date         = {{bya|1966|06}}\n| birth_place        = [[Cheadle Hulme]], [[Stockport]], England\n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = British\n| other_names        = \n| known_for          = \n| education          = [[Cheadle Hulme High School]]<br/>[[Sheffield University]]\n| employer           = [[Caxton Associates]]\n| occupation         = Financier\n| networth           = {{increase}} {{GBP}}485 million <small>(Sunday Times Rich List, 2019)</small>\n| spouse             = Zoe Law\n| children           = \n| parents            = \n| relatives          = \n}}\n'''Andrew Eric Law''' (born June 1966) is a British financier, hedge fund manager and philanthropist. He serves as the chairman and chief executive officer of [[Caxton Associates]], a hedge fund headquartered on [[Berkeley Square]] in London.\n\n==Early life==\nAndrew Eric Law was born in June 1966,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/tGHT8YEuYkqXopv_SB07iDpSVQ4/appointments|title=Andrew Eric LAW - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House)|author=|date=|website=beta.companieshouse.gov.uk|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref> and raised in [[Cheadle Hulme]] near [[Stockport]], England.<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\">Andrew Cave, [https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/newsbysector/banksandfinance/10081784/Outspoken-hedge-fund-boss-who-made-the-journey-from-city-to-city.html Outspoken hedge fund boss who made the journey from city to city], ''The Daily Telegraph'', 26 May 2013</ref><ref name=\"speakersforschoolsandrew\">{{cite web|url=http://www.speakers4schools.org/speakers/andrew-law|title=Andrew Law \u2013 Speakers for Schools|author=|date=|website=www.speakers4schools.org|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref> His father was a mechanical engineer and his mother was a nurse.<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/> He was educated at [[Cheadle Hulme High School]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/> He graduated from the [[University of Sheffield]] in [[Sheffield]], [[South Yorkshire]], with a [[British undergraduate degree classification|First Class honours degree]] in Economics in 1987.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\">{{cite web|url=http://www.lawfamilycharitablefoundation.org/|title=Law Family Charitable Foundation - Andrew & Zo\u00eb Law|author=|date=|website=www.lawfamilycharitablefoundation.org|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"socialfinanceboard\">{{cite web|url=http://www.socialfinance.org.uk/about-us/board-and-team/|title=Social Finance: Board|author=|date=|website=socialfinance.org.uk|accessdate=29 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171021212608/http://www.socialfinance.org.uk/about-us/board-and-team/|archive-date=21 October 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"cnbc\">[https://www.cnbc.com/id/48162061#. Andrew E. Law], ''[[CNBC]]''</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHe started his career in finance at County NatWest, now known as [[NatWest]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/><ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> He then worked as a trader at the [[Chemical Bank]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/><ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/><ref name=\"cnbc\"/> In 1996, he joined [[Goldman Sachs]], later becoming a managing director, where he oversaw [[Investment banking|FICC]].<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/><ref name=\"cnbc\"/>\n\n=== Caxton Associates ===\nHe started working at Caxton Associates in London in 2003.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\" /><ref name=\"cnbc\" /> In 2008, he became its Chief Investment Officer.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\" /><ref name=\"socialfinanceboard\" /><ref name=\"ftsamjones\">Sam Jones, [http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/0ecc2df4-3679-11e3-8ae3-00144feab7de.html Quiet Caxton chief refuses to shout about $1bn gain], ''Financial Times'', 20 October 2013</ref> Since 2012, he has served as its chairman and chief executive officer.<ref name=\"socialfinanceboard\" /><ref name=\"cnbc\" /><ref name=\"ftsamjones\" /> Law is the company's main shareholder.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/article/sunday-times-rich-list-2019-profiles-251-298-lkqrqgnkb|title=Rich List 2019: profiles 251-298=|last=Times|first=The Sunday|date=2019-05-12|access-date=2019-09-20|language=en|issn=0140-0460}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Caxton Associates made \u00a37.3 million profit, down from \u00a395.8 million in 2016.<ref name=\":0\" /> \n\n==Political affiliations==\nBetween May 2010 and January 2015, he donated \u00a3947,911 to the [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative Party]], making him its 11th biggest donor in this period.<ref name=\"ftelizabeth\">Elizabeth Rigby, Gavin Jackson, George Parker, 'Tories double number of big City donors in five years: Miliband attacks 'party of Mayfair hedge funds and Monaco tax avoiders',' ''Financial Times'', 5 February 2015, p. 1, http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/11306cd0-ac94-11e4-beeb-00144feab7de.html#axzz3wTjPW2T4</ref> In May 2017, he gave \u00a3250,000 to the Conservative Party.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cityam.com/264987/party-donors-biggest-names-bank-rolling-conservative|title=Party donors: Here are the big names bank-rolling the Conservative campaign|first=Helen|last=Cahill|date=18 May 2017|website=cityam.com|accessdate=28 January 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\nHe co-chairs the Law Family Charitable Foundation with his wife.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> They support many non-profit organisations, including the [[Policy Exchange]], a think tank based in [[Westminster]].<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> In 2014, they donated \u00a31&nbsp;million to [[The Lowry]] in [[City of Salford|Salford]], where the spaces inside the Main Gallery were renamed The Andrew and Zo\u00eb Law Galleries.<ref name=\"manchestershelina\">Shelina Begum, [http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/business/businessman-andrew-law-wife-zo-7354917 Businessman Andrew Law and wife Zo\u00eb donate \u00a31m to The Lowry], ''Manchester Evening News'', 2 July 2014</ref><ref name=\"thelowrywebsite\">[http://www.thelowry.com/news/2014/07/01/the-lowry-announces-largest-ever-private-donation-and-achieves-5m-capital-funding-target The Lowry announces largest ever private donation and achieves \u00a35m capital funding target], The Lowry, 1 July 2014</ref>\n\nLaw is the chairman of the board of Trustees of Speakers for Schools, which invites public speakers to state schools in the UK.<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> He spoke at the [[Trinity C.E. High School]] in Manchester.<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\"/> He also serves on the Board of Trustees of [[Social Finance UK|Social Finance]].<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/> Additionally, he is a patron of the Hotcourses Foundation, which helps vulnerable schoolchildren in [[Kenya]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nyumbani.org.uk/patrons/|title=Patrons of Nyumbani UK|author=|date=|website=nyumbani.org.uk|accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn an op ed published in ''[[The Huffington Post]]'' in 2014, he called for hedge fund managers to be more philanthropic.<ref>Andrew Law, [http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/andrew-law/the-hedge-fund-formula-fo_b_4115015.html The Hedge Fund Formula For Philanthropy], ''The Huffington Post'', 23 January 2014</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe is married to Zo\u00eb Law<ref name=\"lawfamilycharitablefoundation\"/>, a photographer whose portfolio includes the recent exhibition ''LIFE'' <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.list.co.uk/event/1032513-zoe-law-life/|title=Zoe Law: LIFE|website=The List|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-23}}</ref>,  which features portraits of 21 people who have cancer. The exhibition, which was displayed at The Lowry in Salford Quays in 2019 <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.northernsoul.me.uk/photo-gallery-life-an-exhibition-by-photographer-zoe-law-at-salfords-the-lowry/|title=Photo Gallery: LIFE by Zo\u00eb Law, The Lowry, Salford|date=2019-04-15|website=Northern Soul|language=en-GB|access-date=2019-08-23}}</ref>, was set up to raise awareness of the cancer support provided by the [[Maggie's Centres]]. Zo\u00eb Law was previously a make-up artist whose clients included the British singer [[Dido (singer)|Dido.]] \n\nAccording to The [[Sunday Times Rich List]] in 2019, Law is worth \u00a3485 million.<ref name=\":0\" />\n\nHe is a supporter of the football team, [[Manchester City F.C.]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\" /> He owns \"Manchester City vs Sheffield United\", a 1938 painting by [[L. S. Lowry]].<ref name=\"telegraphandrewcave\" />\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Law, Andrew}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Cheadle Hulme]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Sheffield]]\n[[Category:Goldman Sachs people]]\n[[Category:English hedge fund managers]]\n[[Category:English philanthropists]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) people]]\n[[Category:People educated at Cheadle Hulme School]]\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) donors]]\n[[Category:Bankers from London]]\n", "name_user": "Fayenatic london", "label": "safe", "comment": "Copying fromCategory:English hedge fund managerstoCategory:English financial businesspeopleWikipedia:Categories_for_discussion/Log/2020_February_17#Category:Scottish_stockbrokersusingCat-a-lot", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Andrew_Law_(financier)"}
{"title_page": "Alan Howard (hedge fund manager)", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name         = Alan Howard\n|birth_date   = {{bda|1963|09|11|df=y}}\n|birth_place  = England\n|death_date   = \n|death_place  = \n|residence    = London, England\n|education    = [[Imperial College London]]\n|nationality  = British\n|occupation   = Hedge fund manager\n|known for    = Co-founder of [[Brevan Howard]] Asset Management LLP\n|networth     = GBP \u00a31.76&nbsp;billion <br> US$1.6&nbsp;billion (Forbes, 2019)\n<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/alan-howard/|title=Alan Howard|website=Forbes}}</ref>|spouse       = Sabine Howard (div.)\n|parents      = \n|children     = 4\n}}\n\n'''Alan Howard''' (born September 1963) is a British billionaire [[hedge fund]] manager and co-founder of [[Brevan Howard]] Asset Management LLP.<ref name=independent>{{cite journal|title=The Business On... Alan Howard, Founder, Brevan Howard|journal=[[The Independent]]|date=21 September 2011|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/news/the-business-on-alan-howard-founder-brevan-howard-2358148.html|accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref> In February 2013, ''[[Forbes]]'' listed him as one of the 40 highest-earning hedge fund managers.<ref>{{Citation |url= https://www.forbes.com/lists/2013/hedge-fund-managers-13_land.html |title=The 40 Highest-Earning Hedge Fund Managers & Traders 2013 |date=26 February 2013 |magazine=[[Forbes]] |last=Vardi |first=Nathan }}</ref> In 2014, he was ranked 53rd on the UK's ''[[Sunday Times Rich List]]''.<ref>{{cite web| title=2014 Sunday Times Rich List | url=http://features.thesundaytimes.co.uk/richlist/2014/live/richlist/view/group6/50/rank/#list | accessdate=5 May 2014}}</ref> \nAccording to ''Forbes'', as of 2019, Howard's net worth is $1.6&nbsp;billion.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Early life and education==\nBorn in England to a [[British Jews|Jewish]]<ref name=guadian>{{cite news|author =Andrew Clark|title=Alan Howard: New billionaire on the block|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2010/mar/11/forces-rich-list-alan-howard|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=11 March 2010}}</ref> family, Howard attended [[Hasmonean High School|Hasmonean Grammar School]], Hendon London. After graduating from [[Imperial College London]] with a master's degree,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/alan-howard/|title=Alan Howard |work=Forbes|accessdate=19 March 2013}}</ref> he began his financial career at [[Salomon Brothers]] and worked in the ECU eurobond market.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.efinancialnews.com/homepage/fn100/content/1046717369/alanhoward|title=\"Alan Howard\", Dow Jones Financial News|author=|date=|website=efinancialnews.com|accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHoward served on the New York Federal Reserve's investor advisory committee on financial markets and is one of a group of financial managers, who on occasion, advise New York Federal Reserve officials on economic policy.<ref name=\"Yahoo Finance/Reuters\">{{cite web | url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/brevan-howard-posts-poor-returns-215854867.html | title=Top global hedge fund Brevan Howard takes emerging markets hit | agency=Reuters | date=10 October 2013 | accessdate=18 October 2013 | author=Goldstein, Matthew |author2=Ablan, Jennifer |author3=Wachtel, Katya}}</ref><br>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe was married to Sabine Howard, who is French, and they have four children.<ref name=\"spouse\">{{cite news|title=English Billionaire Alan Howard Settles Ownership Dispute Over Painting For $10 Million|url=http://jewishbusinessnews.com/2013/11/01/english-billionaire-alan-howard-settles-ownership-dispute-over-painting-for-10-million/|accessdate=22 May 2016|publisher=Jewish Business News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fnlondon.com/articles/alan-howard-moves-geneva-20100629|title=Alan Howard moves to Geneva|first=Harriet|last=Agnew|date=|website=fnlondon.com|accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref> They divorced in 2015.\n\nIn 2010, Howard moved from London to [[Geneva]], Switzerland.<ref>[http://www.efinancialnews.com/story/2010-06-29/alan-howard-moves-geneva \"Alan Howard moves to Geneva\" Efinancial News] E financial news</ref> Five years later, he purchased a $14.5&nbsp;million condo in [[Miami]], [[Florida]].<ref name=\"miami condo\">{{cite news|last1=Kallergis|first1=Katherine|title=British billionaire buys at Faena for $14.5M|url=http://therealdeal.com/miami/2015/10/07/british-billionaire-buys-at-faena-for-14-5m/|accessdate=13 February 2016|publisher=The Real Deal}}</ref>\nIn 2017, he returned to London.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-08-21/alan-howard-said-to-return-to-london-after-seven-years-in-geneva|title=Alan Howard Returns to London After 7 Years in Geneva|author=Suzy Waite|date=21 August 2017|website=Bloomberg LP|accessdate=20 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nHoward has been active in Conservative Party circles.<ref name=independent/>\n\nHoward founded the Alan Howard Charitable Foundation which contributes to charities that aim to support Israel and other Jewish causes. The foundation has a central focus on [[Holocaust]] education, the homeless and Israeli film.<ref>[http://www.thejc.com/jc-power-100/the-jc-power-100-numbers-81-90 The Jewish Chronicle \"The JC Power 100: Alan Howard\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104104549/http://www.thejc.com/jc-power-100/the-jc-power-100-numbers-81-90 |date=4 November 2013 }} 5 September 2008</ref> Howard also operates a charitable foundation and supports [[homeless]] charities.<ref name=independent/>\n\nIn 2014, Howard started The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series, which is a collection of conversations, talks, and entertainment by leaders and experts in their respective fields. Each event is intended to raise money for a Jewish centre in London.<ref name=\"The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series\">{{cite web|title=ABOUT THE SERIES|url=https://www.ahf-jw3series.com/|website=The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series|publisher=The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series|accessdate=4 August 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"AHF\">{{cite web|title=ABOUT The Speaker Series|url=https://www.ahf-jw3series.com/about/|website=The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series|publisher=The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series|accessdate=4 August 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Business Insider\">{{cite news|last1=Cook|first1=James|title=Billionaire investor Peter Thiel: 'Always aim for a monopoly. From society's perspective, it's complicated. But from the inside, I always want to have a monopoly.'|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/peter-thiel-talk-in-london-on-business-and-politics-2015-4|accessdate=4 August 2017| publisher=Business Insider|date=1 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, ''[[Reuters]]'' reviewed documents of the Cypriot government which show that Howard requested Cypriot citizenship in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Exclusive: The Brits who won't Brexit|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-eu-conservative-donors-exclus/exclusive-the-brits-who-wont-brexit-idUSKBN1YN191|website=reuters.com|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=20601087&sid=aPaQ1qmwpYmw  Bloomberg, March 2009]\n* [https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/brevan-howard-proves-master-of-hedge-funds-with-four-in-top-100.html Bloomberg, January 2012]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Howard, Alan}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English Jews]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Imperial College London]]\n[[Category:English hedge fund managers]]\n[[Category:English financial businesspeople]]\n[[Category:Jewish British philanthropists]]\n[[Category:British expatriates in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:British billionaires]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) donors]]\n[[Category:People from Hendon]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=October 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2017}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name         = Alan Howard\n|birth_date   = {{bda|1963|09|11|df=y}}\n|birth_place  = England\n|death_date   = \n|death_place  = \n|residence    = London, England\n|education    = [[Imperial College London]]\n|nationality  = British\n|occupation   = Hedge fund manager\n|known for    = Co-founder of [[Brevan Howard]] Asset Management LLP\n|networth     = GBP \u00a31.76&nbsp;billion <br> US$1.6&nbsp;billion (Forbes, 2019)\n<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/alan-howard/|title=Alan Howard|website=Forbes}}</ref>|spouse       = Sabine Howard (div.)\n|parents      = \n|children     = 4\n}}\n\n'''Alan Howard''' (born September 1963) is a British billionaire [[hedge fund]] manager and co-founder of [[Brevan Howard]] Asset Management LLP.<ref name=independent>{{cite journal|title=The Business On... Alan Howard, Founder, Brevan Howard|journal=[[The Independent]]|date=21 September 2011|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/news/the-business-on-alan-howard-founder-brevan-howard-2358148.html|accessdate=3 September 2013}}</ref> In February 2013, ''[[Forbes]]'' listed him as one of the 40 highest-earning hedge fund managers.<ref>{{Citation |url= https://www.forbes.com/lists/2013/hedge-fund-managers-13_land.html |title=The 40 Highest-Earning Hedge Fund Managers & Traders 2013 |date=26 February 2013 |magazine=[[Forbes]] |last=Vardi |first=Nathan }}</ref> In 2014, he was ranked 53rd on the UK's ''[[Sunday Times Rich List]]''.<ref>{{cite web| title=2014 Sunday Times Rich List | url=http://features.thesundaytimes.co.uk/richlist/2014/live/richlist/view/group6/50/rank/#list | accessdate=5 May 2014}}</ref> \nAccording to ''Forbes'', as of 2019, Howard's net worth is $1.6&nbsp;billion.<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\n==Early life and education==\nBorn in England to a [[British Jews|Jewish]]<ref name=guadian>{{cite news|author =Andrew Clark|title=Alan Howard: New billionaire on the block|url=https://www.theguardian.com/business/2010/mar/11/forces-rich-list-alan-howard|work=[[The Guardian]]|date=11 March 2010}}</ref> family, Howard attended [[Hasmonean High School|Hasmonean Grammar School]], Hendon London. After graduating from [[Imperial College London]] with a master's degree,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/alan-howard/|title=Alan Howard |work=Forbes|accessdate=19 March 2013}}</ref> he began his financial career at [[Salomon Brothers]] and worked in the ECU eurobond market.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.efinancialnews.com/homepage/fn100/content/1046717369/alanhoward|title=\"Alan Howard\", Dow Jones Financial News|author=|date=|website=efinancialnews.com|accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHoward served on the New York Federal Reserve's investor advisory committee on financial markets and is one of a group of financial managers, who on occasion, advise New York Federal Reserve officials on economic policy.<ref name=\"Yahoo Finance/Reuters\">{{cite web | url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/brevan-howard-posts-poor-returns-215854867.html | title=Top global hedge fund Brevan Howard takes emerging markets hit | agency=Reuters | date=10 October 2013 | accessdate=18 October 2013 | author=Goldstein, Matthew |author2=Ablan, Jennifer |author3=Wachtel, Katya}}</ref><br>\n\n==Personal life==\nHe was married to Sabine Howard, who is French, and they have four children.<ref name=\"spouse\">{{cite news|title=English Billionaire Alan Howard Settles Ownership Dispute Over Painting For $10 Million|url=http://jewishbusinessnews.com/2013/11/01/english-billionaire-alan-howard-settles-ownership-dispute-over-painting-for-10-million/|accessdate=22 May 2016|publisher=Jewish Business News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fnlondon.com/articles/alan-howard-moves-geneva-20100629|title=Alan Howard moves to Geneva|first=Harriet|last=Agnew|date=|website=fnlondon.com|accessdate=5 August 2018}}</ref> They divorced in 2015.\n\nIn 2010, Howard moved from London to [[Geneva]], Switzerland.<ref>[http://www.efinancialnews.com/story/2010-06-29/alan-howard-moves-geneva \"Alan Howard moves to Geneva\" Efinancial News] E financial news</ref> Five years later, he purchased a $14.5&nbsp;million condo in [[Miami]], [[Florida]].<ref name=\"miami condo\">{{cite news|last1=Kallergis|first1=Katherine|title=British billionaire buys at Faena for $14.5M|url=http://therealdeal.com/miami/2015/10/07/british-billionaire-buys-at-faena-for-14-5m/|accessdate=13 February 2016|publisher=The Real Deal}}</ref>\nIn 2017, he returned to London.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-08-21/alan-howard-said-to-return-to-london-after-seven-years-in-geneva|title=Alan Howard Returns to London After 7 Years in Geneva|author=Suzy Waite|date=21 August 2017|website=Bloomberg LP|accessdate=20 March 2019}}</ref>\n\nHoward has been active in Conservative Party circles.<ref name=independent/>\n\nHoward founded the Alan Howard Charitable Foundation which contributes to charities that aim to support Israel and other Jewish causes. The foundation has a central focus on [[Holocaust]] education, the homeless and Israeli film.<ref>[http://www.thejc.com/jc-power-100/the-jc-power-100-numbers-81-90 The Jewish Chronicle \"The JC Power 100: Alan Howard\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131104104549/http://www.thejc.com/jc-power-100/the-jc-power-100-numbers-81-90 |date=4 November 2013 }} 5 September 2008</ref> Howard also operates a charitable foundation and supports [[homeless]] charities.<ref name=independent/>\n\nIn 2014, Howard started The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series, which is a collection of conversations, talks, and entertainment by leaders and experts in their respective fields. Each event is intended to raise money for a Jewish centre in London.<ref name=\"The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series\">{{cite web|title=ABOUT THE SERIES|url=https://www.ahf-jw3series.com/|website=The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series|publisher=The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series|accessdate=4 August 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"AHF\">{{cite web|title=ABOUT The Speaker Series|url=https://www.ahf-jw3series.com/about/|website=The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series|publisher=The Alan Howard Foundation/JW3 Speaker Series|accessdate=4 August 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"Business Insider\">{{cite news|last1=Cook|first1=James|title=Billionaire investor Peter Thiel: 'Always aim for a monopoly. From society's perspective, it's complicated. But from the inside, I always want to have a monopoly.'|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/peter-thiel-talk-in-london-on-business-and-politics-2015-4|accessdate=4 August 2017| publisher=Business Insider|date=1 May 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019, ''[[Reuters]]'' reviewed documents of the Cypriot government which show that Howard requested Cypriot citizenship in 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=Exclusive: The Brits who won't Brexit|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-britain-eu-conservative-donors-exclus/exclusive-the-brits-who-wont-brexit-idUSKBN1YN191|website=reuters.com|publisher=Reuters|accessdate=20 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.bloomberg.com/apps/news?pid=20601087&sid=aPaQ1qmwpYmw  Bloomberg, March 2009]\n* [https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/brevan-howard-proves-master-of-hedge-funds-with-four-in-top-100.html Bloomberg, January 2012]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Howard, Alan}}\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:English Jews]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Imperial College London]]\n[[Category:English hedge fund managers]]\n[[Category:Jewish British philanthropists]]\n[[Category:British expatriates in Switzerland]]\n[[Category:British billionaires]]\n[[Category:Conservative Party (UK) donors]]\n[[Category:People from Hendon]]\n", "name_user": "Fayenatic london", "label": "safe", "comment": "Copying fromCategory:English hedge fund 